      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house, is essentially a temporary holding account managed by a neutral third party, like a lawyer or a title company. Think of it as a secure, temporary holding spot for the money and documents related to the sale. You need it for the closing because it ensures that both you (the buyer) and the seller fulfill your respective obligations before the property officially changes hands. It keeps the transaction fair and secure for everyone involved.",
