    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so like, who actually holds onto the money while it's sitting there? is it just a bank or someone else? i just wanna make sure it's safe while we wait for the closing date.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money is typically held by a licensed real estate lawyer or a specialized title/escrow company, not just a standard bank account. These professionals are legally bound to hold those funds in a designated, segregated escrow account. This separation is crucial because it protects the funds from being mixed with their own operational money, which is vital for ensuring the money is safe until the final closing documents are signed. They act as the trusted intermediary, making sure the funds are only released when all conditions are met.",
