    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok so if it's a lawyer holding it, what happens if there's a mistake or a dispute during the process? like if the seller doesn't do what they're supposed to, how does the escrow account actually help prevent things from going wrong?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If a dispute arises, the escrow agent—your lawyer or title company—steps in as the impartial referee. They are there to manage the flow of funds according to the terms of your purchase agreement. If the seller fails to meet their obligations, say they refuse to provide clear title, the escrow agent can legally withhold the buyer's funds. This prevents you from losing your deposit while the dispute is resolved, keeping the money safe until the contractual requirements are met.",
      "source": "target",
